  "Both forward and reverse reactions continue at equal rates, with no net change in concentrations": "",
  "The products are continuously removed": "",
  "Dynamic means ongoing motion. At equilibrium, molecules are still reacting (it is not static), but the forward rate equals the reverse rate, so concentrations appear unchanged.": "",
